<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-07-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-07-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="1335" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1335">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 412.00/2.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">American
                                    Ambassador</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 424.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-07-13">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 13, 1911</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has received your No. 692
                            [672] of the 23d ultimo, enclosing copy of an instruction addressed by
                            you to the consular officers in Mexico relative to the course to be
                            pursued by them if they should be called upon by the State Governors or
                            other Mexican officials for information in regard to the damages
                            suffered by American citizens in consequence of the recent
                            revolution.</p>
                        <p>In approving your action in this matter the Department desires to call
                            your attention to instructions which have been issued by it to consular
                            officers, a copy of which has been sent to you, together with further
                            instructions as to the Embassy’s action.</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington Wilson.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>